# Project Structure

Portal is a Next.js 15 business operations platform with comprehensive CRM functionality.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 15, React 19, TailwindCSS, shadcn/ui components
- **Backend**: Next.js API routes, tRPC for typesafe APIs, NextAuth.js/Better Auth
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM 
- **Internationalization**: next-intl for multi-language support (en, zh-CN, zh-HK)
- **File Storage**: AWS S3 integration for file uploads
- **Email**: React Email for templated emails
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS with class-variance-authority for component variants

## Directory Structure

- `/app`: Next.js App Router with locale support `[locale]`
  - `/(auth)`: Authentication pages (login, register, reset password)
  - `/(landing)`: Landing/marketing pages 
  - `/dashboard`: Main application dashboard with CRM features
  - `/api`: Next.js API routes (upload, webhooks, v1 REST endpoints)

- `/components`: React components organized by usage
  - `/ui`: Base shadcn/ui components (button, dialog, form, etc.)
  - `/shared`: Reusable components across sections (combobox, date-pickers, etc.)
  - `/dashboard`: Dashboard-specific components (header, sidebar, etc.)
  - `/landing`: Landing page components
  - `/root`: Root layout components and providers

- `/server`: tRPC server architecture
  - `/routers`: API routers by domain (auth, user, contact, company, team, etc.)
  - `/helper`: Server-side helper functions
  - `trpc.ts`: tRPC setup and context
  - `root.ts`: Main app router combining all sub-routers

- `/drizzle`: Database layer
  - `schema.ts`: Comprehensive database schema (20+ tables)
  - `relations.ts`: Table relationships and foreign keys

- `/lib`: Core utilities and configurations
  - `auth.ts`: NextAuth.js/Better Auth configuration
  - `database.ts`: Database connection and setup
  - `utils.ts`: Common utility functions (cn, isDev)
  - `env.ts`: Environment variable validation
  - `s3.ts`: S3/R2 client configuration
  - `mail.ts`: Email sending configuration

- `/utils`: Application-specific utilities
  - `trpc/`: tRPC client utilities and providers
  - `audit.ts`: Audit logging utilities  
  - `activity.ts`: Activity tracking utilities
  - `api-audit.ts`: API audit logging for REST endpoints

- `/hooks`: Custom React hooks
  - `use-mobile.ts`: Mobile/responsive detection
  - `use-debounce.ts`: Debouncing utilities
  - `use-upload.ts`: File upload hook with S3 integration

- `/emails`: React Email templates
  - `welcome.tsx`: Welcome email template
  - `magic-link.tsx`: Magic link authentication email
  - `password-reset.tsx`: Password reset email

- `/i18n`: Internationalization setup
  - `/locales`: Translation JSON files (en.json, zh-CN.json, zh-HK.json)
  - `routing.ts`: i18n routing configuration
  - `navigation.ts`: Localized navigation helpers

- `/types`: TypeScript type definitions
  - `i18n.ts`: i18n type definitions
  - `audit.ts`: Audit logging types

## Key Features

- **CRM**: Contact management, company management, team collaboration
- **Dashboard**: Analytics, task management, calendar, resource management
- **Authentication**: Email/password, OAuth providers, session management
- **File Upload**: S3 integration with signed URLs and progress tracking
- **Email System**: Templated emails with React Email
- **Audit Trail**: Comprehensive logging of user actions and API calls
- **Multi-language**: Support for English, Chinese Simplified, Chinese Traditional
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first design with responsive components

## Architecture Patterns

- Use App Router for all routing
- Implement locale-based routing with `[locale]` parameter
- Organize components by usage context (ui, shared, domain-specific)
- Use tRPC for typesafe API calls with React Query integration
- Implement comprehensive audit logging for all data modifications
- Use Drizzle ORM with prepared statements for database operations
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns with Tailwind styling
